Mission & Vision

KIPP Endeavor Academy will build and preserve within each student the strong knowledge, skills, and character traits necessary to succesfully obtain a college degree. 

With integrity and compassion, students will have a vested interest in applying learned sills to surpass their own self-concern and better the world around them.

Work Hard. Play Nice.

Hello and welcome to KIPP Endeavor Academy (KEA) - a free public charter school. KIPP Endeavor Academy currently serves approximately 200 students from around Kansas City's urban core.

Read more about KEA

Hello and welcome to KIPP Endeavor Academy (KEA), a free public charter school! KIPP Endeavor Academy currently serves approximately 200 students from around Kansas City's urban core. Our founding group of students is known as the class of "2015," the year they will attend college. KEA presently hosts 5th, 6th and 7th grade students, and will be adding the 8th grade for the 2010-2011 school year.
